Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging and place onto a lined #baking tray{}, skin-side up. Scatter over half the @Chinese five spice{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, add a drizzle of @oil{}, then rub all over the duck.

When the oven is hot, roast the duck on the top shelf for ~{25-30%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the duck is piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} and stir in half the @soy sauce{30%ml}. Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm. Set aside.

While the green beans cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{240%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, remove the @vegetable spring rolls{4} from the packaging and pop onto a #baking tray{}. Bake on the middle shelf until golden and piping hot, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Once cooked, add the remaining garlic and remaining Chinese five spice to the chicken and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @szechuan paste{1%sachet}, @honey{1%tbsp}, @tomato ketchup{1%tbsp} and @water for the sauce{50%ml} and the remaining soy sauce.

Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

When everything's nearly ready, cook the @steamed basmati rice{1} according to pack instructions.

When the duck is piping hot, remove from the oven and drizzle over the @hoisin sauce{64%g}. Return to the oven to glaze, ~{1%minute}.

Transfer your Szechuan chicken, rice and green beans to separate #serving bowls{}. Sprinkle the @cashew nuts{25%g} over the chicken.

Serve your duck and spring rolls on a #platter{} with your @sweet chilli sauce{48%g} in a #small bowl{} on the side for dipping.

Share and tuck in. Enjoy!